se the following text for your answer. Do not make anything up in your answer.\n\nText:\n-----Entities-----\nhuman_readable_id,title,description,degree\n1095,\"\"\"BALANCED SCORECARD\"\"\",\"The Balanced Scorecard is a strategic management technique developed by Kaplan and Norton that provides top management with an integrated set of performance measures from four perspectives: financial, customer, internal business processes, and learning and growth. This approach to performance management ensures that internal systems and processes support customer and financial objectives, encourages integration between departments, and allows for performance measurement and control actions. It is used to align business activities with the vision and strategy of the organization, improve internal and external communications, and monitor organizational performance against strategic goals. The Balanced Scorecard comprises an integrated framework of financial and non-financial performance measures that aim to clarify, communicate, and manage strategy implementation across the four perspectives.\",22\n1096,\"\"\"BALANCED SCORECARD PHILOSOPHY\"\"\",\"\"\"The balanced scorecard philosophy involves setting measures and performance targets across four perspectives: customer, internal business process, learning and growth, and financial, ensuring that these perspectives complement each other.\"\"\",2\n1097,\"\"\"SETTING MEASURES AND PERFORMANCE TARGETS\"\"\",\"\"\"For each perspective in the balanced scorecard, management needs to identify objectives, measures, targets, and initiatives to improve performance.\"\"\",2\n1101,\"\"\"3ES\"\"\",\"\"\"The 3Es stand for economy, efficiency, and effectiveness, which are used to achieve Value for Money (VFM) in the public sector.\"\"\",1\n1098,\"\"\"LEADING AND LAGGING INDICATORS\"\"\",\"\"\"Leading indicators predict future performance, while lagging indicators reflect past performance. Both are used in the balanced scorecard to provide a comprehensive view of performance.\"\"\",1\n1099,\"\"\"CRITICAL SUCCESS FACTOR\"\"\",\"\"\"A performance outcome that an organisation requires to achieve success.\"\"\",1\n1112,\"\"\"KAPLAN AND NORTON\"\"\",\"\"\"Developers of the balanced scorecard approach, which integrates financial and non-financial performance measures.\"\"\",1\n1113,\"\"\"PERFORMANCE MEASURE\"\"\",\"\"\"A quantitative or qualitative characterisation of performance used to evaluate progress toward an objective.\"\"\",1\n1114,\"\"\"OBJECTIVE\"\"\",\"\"\"A specific, measurable statement of what will be done to achieve goals within a defined time frame.\"\"\",1\n1115,\"\"\"INITIATIVES\"\"\",\"\"\"Actions taken to improve performance in line with the objectives and measures identified in the balanced scorecard.\"\"\",1\n1913,\"\"\"PERFORMANCE EVALUATION OF THE PEOPLE'S BANK USING THE BALANCED SCORECARD APPROACH\"\"\",\"\"\"The People's Bank uses the balanced scorecard approach to evaluate its performance. The bank's vision is to be 'the bank that gives back to its customers,' and it aims to help the people and businesses of Nawkrei live better lives and achieve their ambitions. The bank's values include putting customers' needs first, making business simple, and making a difference to the communities they serve. The balanced scorecard helps the bank measure performance across financial, customer, internal business processes, and innovation and learning perspectives.\"\"\",1\n1937,\"\"\"INTERNAL BUSINESS PROCESS PERSPECTIVE\"\"\",\"\"\"This perspective focuses on having an effective and efficient administration. Measures include the number of times a guest request is not received at the resort prior to arrival and the average number of corrections to booking due to administrative errors.\"\"\",1\n1938,\"\"\"INNOVATION AND LEARNING PERSPECTIVE\"\"\",\"\"\"This perspective aims to match leading competitor's facilities. Measures include the number of in-room appliances offered by rivals but not by Hammocks Co 